A basic module will have in the Grid.js file:

[code]
dojo.provide("phpr.MyModule.Grid");

dojo.declare("phpr.MyModule.Grid", phpr.Default.Grid, {
});
[/code]

This is the obligatory code for the file,
but there are other functions that can be re-written for customize the layout:

[emph]constructor:function(/*String*/updateUrl, /*Object*/main, /*Int*/ id)[/emph]

The function init and render the Grid.
Re-write it if you need extra action before the render of the grid
or for add external function with dojo.subscribe() like the Main does.

[emph]setUrl:function()[/emph]

Set the url for get the data from the server.
Change it if your module use other function than jsonList or extra parameters.

[emph]setNode:function()[/emph]

Set the node where put the grid.
If you use other div than gridBox, change it in this function.

[emph]showTags:function()[/emph]

Draw the tags in the tagsBox for the current module.
Re-write this function if you don't want to display the tags or set special parameters to the URL.

[emph]useIdInGrid:function()[/emph]

Return true if you want to draw the ID on the grid, false if not.

[emph]usePencilForEdit:function()[/emph]

Return true if you want to draw the pencil icon for edit the row, false if not.

[emph]useCheckbox:function()[/emph]

Return true if you want to show the check box in the grid list, false if not.

[emph]customGridLayout:function(meta)[/emph]

Use this function for set custom grid layout.
The function is called after all the other field layout are set.

[emph]setClickEdit:function()[/emph]

Set if each field is editable with one or two clicks.

[emph]setExportButton:function(meta)[/emph]

Render the export button if there is any row.
Change this function if you for example, don't want the export button.

[emph]exportData:function()[/emph]

Open a new window in CSV mode.
Re-write the function if your URL for the export is different than csvList or you have more parameters.

[emph]canEdit:function(inRowIndex)[/emph]

heck the access of the item for the user.
Return true if has write or admin access.
Change this function if your access policy is different than the default.

[emph]updateData:function()[/emph]

Delete the cache for this grid.
Re-write this function for provide a correct way to delete all the cache used in the grid.
